http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Campaign-on-wearing-helmets-begins/article14002352.ece

Superintendent of Police Amit Singh launched a helmet awareness campaign by greeting two-wheeler riders and pillion riders here on Saturday.Ahead of the enforcement of rule of compulsory wearing helmets, the police chose to reach out to two-wheeler riders by giving a red rose and a leaflet detailing road safety norms instead of imposing a fine or issuing challans.The campaign kicked off with a group of traffic police, women police constables, and employees working in private organisations wearing helmet by both two-wheeler riders and pillion going around the main streets in the city with the banners and placards with slogans –‘Wear Helmet Avoid death’.